  <text>
     <body>
     <div type="encomium">
   <l>CAn I declare, or any els,</l>
   <l>what they deserue to haue,</l>
   <l>That labour much, and paines doe take,</l>
   <l>mens soules to feede and saue?</l>
   <l>But whatsoeuer is their hire,</l>
   <l>at mans vnthankefull hand,</l>
   <l>They shalbe sure for to enioy,</l>
   <l>at length the quiet land.</l>
   <l>Which God wil giue vnto eche one,</l>
   <l>that vertue doth attend.</l>
   <l>And also here it shall appeare,</l>
   <l>that he will be their friend.</l>
   <l>Worke on therefore ô Robinson,</l>
   <l>cease not thy skill to showe.</l>
   <l>For well it will be with the good,</l>
   <l>when wicked are in woe.</l>
   <signed>Tho. Buckminster.</signed>
</div>
